00:45:12.065 --> 00:45:13.190
that we've developed today.

00:45:18.690 --> 00:45:19.360
Yes.

00:45:19.360 --> 00:45:21.540
AUDIENCE: What is the most
dangerous kind of decay?

00:45:21.540 --> 00:45:23.457
MICHAEL SHORT: What is
the most dangerous kind

00:45:23.457 --> 00:45:25.320
of decay to be exposed to?

00:45:25.320 --> 00:45:28.640
So in this case, you'd want to
say the energy of the particle

00:45:28.640 --> 00:45:31.440
is held constant, and the
number of those particles

00:45:31.440 --> 00:45:33.150
is held constant.

00:45:33.150 --> 00:45:35.643
And actually, we're going
to answer this question

00:45:35.643 --> 00:45:37.560
when we get to medical
and biological effects.

00:45:37.560 --> 00:45:39.163
But let's do a little
flash word now.

00:45:39.163 --> 00:45:41.580
Let's assume, if you want to
see which one of these decays

00:45:41.580 --> 00:45:44.610
is most dangerous, we'll
have to say constant--

00:45:47.210 --> 00:45:54.010
constant-- energy of decay,
constant activity, and what

00:45:54.010 --> 00:45:56.850
else can we hold constant?

00:45:56.850 --> 00:45:59.070
Well, constant you.

00:45:59.070 --> 00:46:02.360
Let's say the same number of
particles end up hitting you.

00:46:02.360 --> 00:46:07.080
That depends on whether they're
inside or outside your body.

00:46:07.080 --> 00:46:10.680
If you were to ingest
material, then alphas

00:46:10.680 --> 00:46:13.200
would be your worst
because alpha particles

00:46:13.200 --> 00:46:16.650
are massive and
charged nuclei, which

00:46:16.650 --> 00:46:18.630
means they interact very
strongly with matter

00:46:18.630 --> 00:46:19.210
around them.

00:46:19.210 --> 00:46:21.182
So if you ingest
them and they end up

00:46:21.182 --> 00:46:23.640
incorporating into your cells,
where they can just get next

00:46:23.640 --> 00:46:26.580
to DNA, they can
just blast it apart.

00:46:26.580 --> 00:46:29.460
However, an alpha source
of equal strength held

00:46:29.460 --> 00:46:31.920
in your hand would do nothing.

00:46:31.920 --> 00:46:35.142
The dead skin cells are enough
to stop alpha particles.

00:46:35.142 --> 00:46:36.600
And we're going to
find out exactly

00:46:36.600 --> 00:46:38.850
why when we look at
the range and stopping

00:46:38.850 --> 00:46:41.540
power of different
particles and matter.

00:46:41.540 --> 00:46:44.950
From the outside, alphas won't
really get through your skin.

00:46:44.950 --> 00:46:48.110
Betas might get through a little
bit of your skin, but not much.

00:46:48.110 --> 00:46:50.660
Gamma rays will mostly
go right through you.

00:46:50.660 --> 00:46:54.650
It's neutrons that
are the real killers.

00:46:54.650 --> 00:46:58.190
Those neutrons are
heavy but uncharged.

00:46:58.190 --> 00:47:00.380
So they interact
kind of strongly.

00:47:00.380 --> 00:47:02.590
When they do hit,
they pack a wallop

00:47:02.590 --> 00:47:04.130
and they do a lot of damage.

00:47:04.130 --> 00:47:05.900
And they're mean
free path, and you is

00:47:05.900 --> 00:47:07.920
on the order of 10 centimeters.

00:47:07.920 --> 00:47:11.030
So a neutron source from the
outside can do a lot of damage

00:47:11.030 --> 00:47:12.112
from the outside.

00:47:12.112 --> 00:47:13.820
The alphas and the
betas would be stopped

00:47:13.820 --> 00:47:15.530
by your skin and clothes.

00:47:15.530 --> 00:47:18.072
The gamma rays, almost all of
them will go right through you.

00:47:18.072 --> 00:47:20.322
And you guys will actually
have to do this calculation

00:47:20.322 --> 00:47:22.010
to find out how many
gamma rays would

00:47:22.010 --> 00:47:23.803
you absorb from a
gamma ray emission,

00:47:23.803 --> 00:47:25.220
and how many go
right through you.

00:47:25.220 --> 00:47:28.760
The hint is most
of them get out.

00:47:28.760 --> 00:47:30.590
So there's an exam
question we used

00:47:30.590 --> 00:47:33.080
to ask in 22.01 that I was
asked during the first exam,

00:47:33.080 --> 00:47:37.340
is you've got four cookies, an
alpha emitter, a beta emitter,

00:47:37.340 --> 00:47:41.690
a gamma emitter, and a neutron
emitter of constant energy

00:47:41.690 --> 00:47:42.890
and activity.

00:47:42.890 --> 00:47:44.940
You must do one
of the following.

00:47:44.940 --> 00:47:48.320
You have to hold one in
your hand at arm's length.

00:47:48.320 --> 00:47:50.270
You have to put
one in your pocket.

00:47:50.270 --> 00:47:55.400
You have to eat one, and you
have to give one to a friend.

00:47:55.400 --> 00:47:58.582
What do you do and why?

00:47:58.582 --> 00:48:00.025
Anyone have an idea?

00:48:03.400 --> 00:48:03.940
Pop quiz.

00:48:03.940 --> 00:48:05.220
Yeah?

00:48:05.220 --> 00:48:08.323
AUDIENCE: Probably give the
